<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="13" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811f.812/756a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">To the Diplomatic Officers of the United States in
                                Latin America.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Circular—Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President has found it impossible to proceed to Panama in July, and
                            in consequence the proposed ceremonies attending the celebration <pb facs="0131" n="15" xml:id="pg_15"/> of the opening of the Panama
                            Canal have been abandoned. The President, therefore, regrets that he is
                            unable to extend to the Ministers of Foreign Affairs of the American
                            Republics the invitation mentioned in Department’s telegram January 16th
                            [sic] last.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>